thumbnail: "src":"https://i.vimeocdn.com/video/1242949684-e71a83bd5a901a2f5a55dacfb7e711a67621d9218b7a9ef09cff7711d8c625af-d_190x107""src_2x":"https://i.vimeocdn.com/video/1242949684-e71a83bd5a901a2f5a55dacfb7e711a67621d9218b7a9ef09cff7711d8c625af-d_380x214""width":190"height":107"id":1242949684duration: "raw":30"formatted":"00:30"clip: "id":605955266"title":"LÖWEN MANUFACTUR: DER ALCHEMIST""description":"Der Weg zur Löwen-Manufactur führt durch die Gassen der Lübecker Innenstadt. Vorbei an einigen anderen Apotheken. Werbung für Kopfschmerzmittel und Gelenkschmerzen sticht einem ins Auge. Leuchtreklame. Blinklichter. Je heller es leuchtet desto stärker kommen die Kunden. So wirkt es zumindest. Und dann am Ende der Gasse liegt sie: Die Löwen Manufactur.nIn einem roten Backsteinhaus. Unscheinbar aber irgendwie ehrfürchtig. Schon beim ersten Betreten wird klar: Das ist keine Apotheke - das ist eine Wohltat. Eine Oase für alle Sinne. Etwas ganz Besonderes. Ich würde sogar sagen: Unvergleichlich. Marcus Niendorf und seine Frau Dietlind Wolf kümmern sich hinreißend um die Manufactur. Mit einer Liebe Leidenschaft und Hingabe die ich so noch nicht erlebt habe. nDieses warme Gefühl die Sensibilität für die Natur und die Liebe für die Produkte - das macht die Löwen Manufactur zu einem ganz besonderen Ort.nDirector: Juliane TaudtDoP: Luca HainProducer: Nina GauslingExec Producer: Mira UmLight & Sound: Raik LingnernEdit: Nik KohlerEdit Socials: Luca Hain & Jona WinklerGrading: Hans HartmannSound Design: Kian DjaliliPost Producer: Dorothee PreutnAgency: Bureau Elias Sturm Production: 27 Kilometer Entertainment GmbHClient: Löwen-Manufactur Lübeck""uploaded_on":"2021-09-15 16:49:41""uploaded_on_relative":"3 months ago""uploaded_on_full":"Wednesday September 15 2021 at 4:49 PM EST""is_spatial":false"is_hdr":false"is_dolby_vision":false"privacy"author: "@type":"Person""name":"Juliane Taudt""url":"https://vimeo.com/julianetaudt"}"potentialAction""@type":"ViewAction""target":"vimeo://app.vimeo.com/videos/605955266"}"duration":"PT00H00M30S""interactionStatistic":["@type":"InteractionCounter""interactionType":"http://schema.org/CommentAction""userInteractionCount":0}"@type":"InteractionCounter""interactionType":"http://schema.org/LikeAction""userInteractionCount":0}"@type":"InteractionCounter""interactionType":"http://schema.org/WatchAction""userInteractionCount":75"@type":"VideoObject""@context":"http://schema.org"}"itemListElement":["@type":"ListItem""position":1"item""@id":"https://vimeo.com/julianetaudt""name":"Juliane Taudt"}}"@type":"ListItem""position":2"item""@id":"https://vimeo.com/julianetaudt/videos""name":"Videos"}"@type":"BreadcrumbList""@context":"http://schema.org"    </script>owner: <end>

Forever.Silence because you don&'t talk "about it".nThe desire to have a child. It&'s a warm feeling an exciting tingle. The great hope. But the desire to have children can also be deep pain endless emptiness and the darkest time of life. Many experience it but only a few talk about it. Unfulfilled desire to have children is not a taboo it is a reality.nIn this film three women tell their story.nThe desire for a child accompanied by six miscarriages until finally giving up.A desire to have children with the certainty that you will never be able to have one&'s own child.A desire to have a child that began in great happiness and then ended in a tragedy.nAll three women have experienced different things but they are united by one thing: deep pain.nDirected by Juliane TaudtDirector of Photography // Marco LowesEditor // Nikolaus KohlerColorist // Nadia Khairat Gómez David CastañónComposer // Alexander MaschkeSounddesign // ELEVEN Creative Audio""uploaded_on":"2021-05-09 08:31:01""uploaded_on_relative":"7 months ago""uploaded_on_full":"Sunday May 9 2021 at 8:31 AM EST""is_spatial":false"is_hdr":false"is_dolby_vision":false"privacy"author: "@type":"Person""name":"Juliane Taudt""url":"https://vimeo.com/julianetaudt"}"potentialAction""@type":"ViewAction""target":"vimeo://app.vimeo.com/videos/547124993"}"duration":"PT00H10M25S""interactionStatistic":["@type":"InteractionCounter""interactionType":"http://schema.org/CommentAction""userInteractionCount":0}"@type":"InteractionCounter""interactionType":"http://schema.org/LikeAction""userInteractionCount":2}"@type":"InteractionCounter""interactionType":"http://schema.org/WatchAction""userInteractionCount":109"@type":"VideoObject""@context":"http://schema.org"}"itemListElement":["@type":"ListItem""position":1"item""@id":"https://vimeo.com/julianetaudt""name":"Juliane Taudt"}}"@type":"ListItem""position":2"item""@id":"https://vimeo.com/julianetaudt/videos""name":"Videos"}"@type":"BreadcrumbList""@context":"http://schema.org"    </script>owner: <end>

And to be honest I don&'t really know much about art either. nThen our film came along - and my personal journey began. My journey into Paul&'s life which he shared with me openly and authentically. My journey into his head during the creation of a painting. It accompanies us for a whole life shows who we are makes touches perceptible and feelings visible. Our skin. It is important to listen to it. To take it first. To nurture it. To honour it.nI interviewed six people for the new Eucerin Brand Campaign. Together we remembered the time when itching pain pinching hiding or even a life-changing diagnosis was part of their lifes. Six real people let me get up close and personal - to the point where Eucerin changed their lives. For them Eucerin is so much more than just medical skin care. Eucerin is trust security and a positive attitude to life.nThank you for letting me be part of this incredibly touching campaign full of warm hearted people and friends.nClient // Beiersdorf thumbnail: "src":"https://i.vimeocdn.com/video/997741338-00229a932ab49dcd3653e7c4b39b243a11790327482b19ad7a0a4004607d0ab3-d_190x107""src_2x":"https://i.vimeocdn.com/video/997741338-00229a932ab49dcd3653e7c4b39b243a11790327482b19ad7a0a4004607d0ab3-d_380x214""width":190"height":107"id":997741338duration: "raw":98"formatted":"01:38"clip: "id":480974596"title":"MODIFIED VIEW""description":"As a person who is in the public eye he or she is subject to constant observation. Others think they know you better than you know yourself. But who are you actually? And how are you? For BOSS Eyewear and VOGUE Germany Stefanie Giesinger and Wana Limar have dared to look at and within themselves. They have taken on a new perspective. I was touched by how they opened up to me. Above all Stefanie showed a side of herself in the interview that I had never seen before. I have met and interviewed Steffi many times before - but this time it was different. During our conversation she was so incredibly reflected self-critical and unsparingly honest with herself that I almost forgot the camera. We had a real deep talk from which I myself took a lot. And it&'s exactly these situations that I love about my job: when an interview turns into a familiar and honest conversation just like with a good bottle of red wine :)nClient // BOSS Eyewear for VOGUE GermanyTalents // Stefanie Giesinger & Wana LimarDirector // Juliane TaudtDoP // Marco Lowes1st AC // Tobias BloierHair & Make Up // Diana DonkorStyling // Ricarda VenjacobCreative Producer // Clara BöhmEdit // Nikolaus KohlerGrading // Delfina Mayer""uploaded_on":"2020-11-18 17:14:49""uploaded_on_relative":"1 year ago""uploaded_on_full":"Wednesday November 18 2020 at 5:14 PM EST""is_spatial":false"is_hdr":false"is_dolby_vision":false"privacy"author: "@type":"Person""name":"Juliane Taudt""url":"https://vimeo.com/julianetaudt"}"potentialAction""@type":"ViewAction""target":"vimeo://app.vimeo.com/videos/480974596"}"duration":"PT00H01M38S""interactionStatistic":["@type":"InteractionCounter""interactionType":"http://schema.org/CommentAction""userInteractionCount":0}"@type":"InteractionCounter""interactionType":"http://schema.org/LikeAction""userInteractionCount":2}"@type":"InteractionCounter""interactionType":"http://schema.org/WatchAction""userInteractionCount":160"keywords":"[FashionModelProjectionsProjektionenSunglassesBOSS EyewearBrandedCommercialWana LimarBOSSVOGUEVOGUE GermanyStefanie Giesinger]""@type":"VideoObject""@context":"http://schema.org"}"itemListElement":["@type":"ListItem""position":1"item""@id":"https://vimeo.com/julianetaudt""name":"Juliane Taudt"}}"@type":"ListItem""position":2"item""@id":"https://vimeo.com/julianetaudt/videos""name":"Videos"}"@type":"BreadcrumbList""@context":"http://schema.org"    </script>owner: <end>

thumbnail: "src":"https://i.vimeocdn.com/video/901934221-866bab14998a825217fc1db411f566edb42a937c6cbbd8a28364c2f208e33423-d_190x107""src_2x":"https://i.vimeocdn.com/video/901934221-866bab14998a825217fc1db411f566edb42a937c6cbbd8a28364c2f208e33423-d_380x214""width":190"height":107"id":901934221duration: "raw":215"formatted":"03:35"clip: "id":424778001"title":"STEFAN MILEV""description":"STEFAN MILEVnAlthough Stefan lives in Berlin and speaks German I wanted to do the interview with him in English. I think that if you give an interview in another language you think more consciously about every single word. But Stefan wasn&'t really enthusiastic about the idea at first. He was afraid that he would not be able to formulate his answers as well as in German. But he gave me and my idea a chance. The result was a wonderful very close interview which would not have had half as much effect in German. The search for the right words and the slight embarrassment characterize Stefan in a wonderful and likeable way. It is so real and so pure. Thank you Stefan for your trust. I love our film.nClient // Hugo Boss Condé NastDirector // Juliane TaudtDoP // Marco LowesEdit // Nicola PowellModel // Katerina TannenbaumPhotographer // Stefan MilevMake Up // Patrick GlatthaarHair // Sina VelkeStyling // Nina GollongArt Director // Mina HashemiProject Manager // Janine Ginzel""uploaded_on":"2020-06-01 09:29:22""uploaded_on_relative":"1 year ago""uploaded_on_full":"Monday June 1 2020 at 9:29 AM EST""is_spatial":false"is_hdr":false"is_dolby_vision":false"privacy"author: "@type":"Person""name":"Juliane Taudt""url":"https://vimeo.com/julianetaudt"}"potentialAction""@type":"ViewAction""target":"vimeo://app.vimeo.com/videos/424778001"}"duration":"PT00H03M35S""interactionStatistic":["@type":"InteractionCounter""interactionType":"http://schema.org/CommentAction""userInteractionCount":0}"@type":"InteractionCounter""interactionType":"http://schema.org/LikeAction""userInteractionCount":0}"@type":"InteractionCounter""interactionType":"http://schema.org/WatchAction""userInteractionCount":188"@type":"VideoObject""@context":"http://schema.org"}"itemListElement":["@type":"ListItem""position":1"item""@id":"https://vimeo.com/julianetaudt""name":"Juliane Taudt"}}"@type":"ListItem""position":2"item""@id":"https://vimeo.com/julianetaudt/videos""name":"Videos"}"@type":"BreadcrumbList""@context":"http://schema.org"    </script>owner: <end>

I&'d heard from colleagues that she&'s not always easy. As if I prepared myself extra intensively for the production and categorized my interview questions from "easy going" to "better not ask if the mood doesn&'t allow it". On the day of shooting itself I experienced an extremely focused and passionate Elizaveta. She carries her heart on her tongue - and I liked that a lot. We got along very well right from the start and I found a direct approach to her. I experienced the interview incredibly intense. Each of her answers was so precise so clever so complex. That impressed me. In the end we sat on the icy cold and windy beach of the Baltic Sea for almost an hour.
